content:
When you enable time zone support, CRM Analytics converts date-time values in datasets to the selected time zone. This is important for accurate views of data specific to a particular region. 

By default, CRM Analytics treats all date-time values as being in GMT. When you enable time zone support, CRM Analytics converts date-time values from GMT to your selected time zone.

Time zone enabled dashboards use converted date-time values from datasets instead of the original values. To enable custom time zone support, refresh connected objects by syncing them and datasets by running related recipes or dataflows. 

Values in new DateTime fields are assumed to be GMT, and are converted to the selected time zone. A GMT field is included to ensure the dataset still works with existing dashboards.

This feature lets dashboard viewers see data in a time zone that's relevant to them, providing accurate views of case creation and other data specific to a particular region.
title: Understanding Time Zone Support in CRM Analytics
